A 63 - year - old Dover woman died Friday from injuries she sustained in a May 12 crash on U.S. Route 113 in Georgetown .
According to the Delaware State Police , Anezia Valette was a passenger in a 1999 Toyota Corolla driven by 37 - year - old Marie Voltaire of Dover .
Police said the accident occurred around 3:40 p.m. as Voltaire was driving in the right lane of U.S. Route 113 just north of Speedway Road .
For an unknown reason , police said the Corolla drifted into the left lane , the left turn lane and then the grass median where it struck a fully marked DSP 2013 Chevrolet Tahoe head on .
